When you search for:

https://www.google.com/search?q=FastAPI

Everything after the ? is a query parameter.

?q=FastAPI

Here:

q = parameter name
FastAPI = value

Google reads it as:

Search for "FastAPI".

More examples
/products?category=laptop

means:

Show only laptops.

/users?age=25

means:

Show users whose age is 25.

/courses?level=beginner

means:

Show beginner courses.

Path Parameter vs Query Parameter
Path Parameter	Query Parameter
Identifies a specific resource	Filters or modifies the request
/course/5	/courses?level=beginner
Course ID is required	Filter is optional

Think of it like this:

/course/5

means:

Give me this exact course.

Whereas:

/courses?level=beginner

means:

Give me courses, but only the beginner ones.
